{
  "texts": [
    "SLP must align with prevailing practice if it intends to continue to prosper as a discipline.",
    "For some suggested best practices for authors, peer reviewers, editors with reference to accountability, transparency, and confidentiality see Leung et al., 2023.",
    "AI will significantly boost research productivity and open new avenues for discovery.",
    "For example, examining the language errors that LLMs make vis-à-vis language errors that a child with delayed language disorder or a person with aphasia makes could provide insight into language disorders while also informing ways to fine-tune LLMs (Ford et al., 2024).",
    "The National Artificial Intelligence Institute for Exceptional Education has even called on SLPs to join interdisciplinary research teams (Miller et al., 2025)."
  ]
}